.TH MIN-COMMANDER 1 "2026-01-31" "2.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
min-commander \- simple, keyboard-driven terminal file manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B min-commander
.SH DESCRIPTION
Min Commander is a simple, keyboard-driven terminal file manager as an alternative to macOS Finder, inspired by the classic Norton Commander.
.PP
The program provides a dual-panel view for efficient file management directly in the terminal.
.SH USAGE
Start the program with:
.PP
.B min-commander
.PP
.SH KEYBOARD SHORTCUTS
.TP
.B Tab
Switch between panels
.TP
.B ↑/↓
Navigate in file list
.TP
.B PgUp/PgDn
Scroll 10 entries up/down
.TP
.B Enter
Open directory
.TP
.B Backspace
Go to parent directory
.TP
.B c
Copy file/directory
.TP
.B r
Move file/directory
.TP
.B d
Delete file/directory
.TP
.B h
Show/hide hidden files
.TP
.B q, Ctrl+C
Quit program
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/bin/min-commander
The executable program
